MoCA

Source: R/data.R
MOCA.Rd

MoCA data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(MOCA)

Format

A data frame with 8388 observations and 59 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with factor levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • PTID character Participant ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 2, ..., 10457

  • VISCODE character Visit code

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • VISDATE Date Assessment MCDATE when present; otherwise Registry EXAMDATE Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • TRAILS character Trails

    • ADNIGO: 1=Correct; 0=Incorrect

    • ADNI2: 1=Correct; 0=Incorrect

    • ADNI4: 0=Incorrect; 1=Correct
